<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-478-122  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 478 122.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  July 31 1989 v6 n30 p17(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MFS makes foray into data services. (Metropolitan Fiber Systems)(includes related article on the range of MFS services)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metropolitan Fiber Systems (MFS) is known mostly as a low-costalternative for voice telephone services but the company isincreasing emphasis on digital data services.andP;  MFS plans toinstall fiber optic networks in the business districts of 20 largecities by the end of 1990.andP;  The company lures its customers withvoice services then, once their reliability is established, triesto convert them to its data services, priced on the average 15percent less than comparable Bell regional holding companyservices.andP;  The company has built networks in Baltimore, Chicago,Boston, Minneapolis and Philadelphia.andP;  Networks are being built inLos Angeles, San Francisco and Houston, with others planned forWashington DC and New York.andP;  Chicago is the only network breakingeven.andP;  Company officials expect it to show a profit by the end ofOct 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     OutlookMarketingData CommunicationsFiber OpticsNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>